<head>BATTLE ARRAY</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">戰陣</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SHAPE PRODUCED by ARMIES PREPARING for BATTLE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[GENERAL/SPECIFIC]</p>
<p>[NOUN/VERB/PARTICLE]</p>
<p>1. The general term for a battle array is zhèn 陣.</p>
<p>[GENERAL], [NOUN!]</p>
<p>2. Chén 陳 refers to the making of a battle array.</p>
<p>[GENERAL], [VERB!]</p>
<p>3. Yàn háng 鴈行／雁行 "alignment of troops at the front of the battle line".</p>
<p>[SPECIFIC], [TECHNICAL-TERM]</p>
<p>4. Yú lí 魚麗 refers to a famous way of arranging the totality of one's military forces in Spring and Autumn times. ZUO Huan 5.</p>
<p>[SPECIFIC], [TECHNICAL-TERM]; [[RARE]]</p>
        </div>
